k%20from%20wherever%20he%20had%20gone%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20police%20left%20David's%20body%20at%20the%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20yelled%20for%20my%20other%20son%20and%20daughter%20who%20live%20with%20me%2C%20then%20found%20my%20phone%20and%20called%20911.%20The%20police%20were%20the%20first%20to%20respond.%20I%20realized%20that%20they%20needed%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20David's%20death%20wasn't%20suspicious%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20to%20be%20sure%20I%20hadn't%20killed%20my%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20quickly%20became%20clear%20this%20was%20a%20natural%20death.%20We'd%20later%20learn%2C%20after%20a%20private%20autopsy%2C%20that%20David%20had%20another%20heart%20attack.%20Satisfied%20that%20there%20was%20no%20foul%20play%2C%20the%20police%20started%20getting%20back%20in%20their%20cruisers.%20I%20was%20shocked%20%E2%80%94%20my%20son%20was%20still%20dead%20in%20his%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20officers%20explained%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20call%20a%20funeral%20home.%20While%20we%20waited%20for%20the%20funeral%20home%20to%20arrive%2C%20my%20other%20children%20had%20time%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20David.%20Then%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20tidying%20his%20room%20so%20the%20funeral%20home%20workers%20would%20have%20easier%20access%20to%20remove%20his%20body.%20It%20was%20the%20strangest%20thing%2C%20cleaning%20while%20my%20dead%20son%20was%20in%20his%20bed%2C%20feet%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20David%20around%20noon%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20until%206%20p.m.%20that%20his%20body%20was%20taken%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20daughter%20moved%20into%20the%20room%20where%20David%20died%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20lives%20in%20a%20small%20condo.%20Before%20David%20died%2C%20he%20and%20my%20daughter%20each%20had%20a%20bedroom%2C%20while%20their%20younger%20brother%20slept%20on%20a%20Murphy%20bed%20in%20the%20dining%20room.%20With%20David%20gone%2C%20we%20were%20pragmatic%3A%20an%20empty%20bedroom%20simply%20didn't%20make%20sense.%3C%