20the%20holidays%20when%20everyone%20else%20is%20drinking.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ashley%20Couto)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stay-sober-during-holidays-tips-advice-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IMF%20Warns%20India%20on%20Debt%20Concerns%2C%20Says%20It%20May%20Exceed%20100%25%20of%20GDP%3B%20Centre%20Disagrees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F01025517%2F16953090889_059d966c4e_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20warned%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20general%20government%20debt%20may%20exceed%20100%25%20of%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20in%20the%20medium%20term%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fimf-cautions-india-on-govt-debt-vulnerabilities-centre-disagrees-123121901166_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20that%20long-term%20risks%20are%20high%20because%20the%20country%20needs%20considerable%20investment%20to%20improve%20resilience%20to%20climate%20stresses%20and%20natural%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20suggests%20that%20new%20and%20preferably%20concessional%20sources%20of%20financing%20are%20needed%2C%20as%20well%20as%20greater%20private%20sector%20investment%20and%20carbon%20pricing%20or%20equivalent%20mechanism%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20IMF%20said%20in%20its%20annual%20Article%20IV%20consultation%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20report%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20surveillance%20function%20under%20the%20Articles%20of%20Agreement%20with%20member%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%2C%20however%2C%20disagreed%2C%20saying%20that%20sovereign%20debt%20risks%20are%20limited%20as%20it%20is%20mainly%20denominated%20in%20domestic%20currency%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EK.V.%20Subramanian%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20at%20the%20IMF%2C%20said%20the%20IMF%E2%80%99s%20assertion%20that%20the%20baseline%20carries%20the%20risk%20that%20debt%20would%20exceed%20100%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20the%20medium%20term%20in%20the%20event%20of%20shocks%20which%20India%20has%20experienced%20historically%20sounds%20extreme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20same%20can%20be%20said%20of%20the%20staff%20prognosis%20that%20debt%20sustainability%20risks%20are%20high%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20The%20risks%20from%20sovereign%20debt%20are%20very%20limited%20as%20it%20is%20predominantly%20denominated%20in%20domestic%20currency.%20Despite%20the%20multitude%20of%20shocks%2C%20the%20global%20economy%20has%20faced%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20debt-to-GDP%20ratio%20at%20the%20general%20government%20level%20has%20barely%20increased%20from%2081%25%20in%202005-06%20to%2084%25%20in%202021-22%2C%20and%20back%20to%2081%25%20in%202022-23%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%5C%22%3Ereclassified%3C%2Fa%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20exchange%20rate%20regime%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstabilised%20arrangement%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20India%20disputes%20this%2C%20emphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20exchange%20rate%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20Article%20IV%20report%2C%20the%20IMF%20gave%20a%20fairly%20optimistic%20outlook%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20saying%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20grow%20faster%20than%20the%20fund%E2%80%99s%20forecast%20of%206.3%25%20in%20the%20current%20and%20next%20fiscal%20years%20if%20the%20government%20undertakes%20key%20structural%20reforms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-12-20%2Fmodi-says-india-looking-into-us-allegations-of-murder-plot-ft%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20accompanying%20statement%20to%20its%20report%2C%20IMF%20said%20that%20India%20needs%20%E2%80%9Cambitious%E2%80%9D%20fiscal%20consolidation%20over%20the%20medium%20term%20in%20order%20to%20curb%20its%20public%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sharp%20global%20growth%20slowdown%20in%20the%20near%20term%20would%20affect%20India%20through%20trade%20and%20financial%20channels.%20Further%20global%20supply%20disruptions%20could%20cause%20recurrent%20commodity%20price%20volatility%2C%20increasing%20fiscal%20pressures%20for%20India.%20Domestically%2C%20weather%20shocks%20could%20reignite%20inflationary%20pressures%20and%20prompt%20further%20food%20export%20restrictions.%20On%20the%20upside%2C%20stronger%20than%20expected%20consumer%20demand%20and%20private%20investment%20would%20raise%20growth%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteps%20to%20bring%20down%20public%20debt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20finance%20minister%C2%A0Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Flooking-at-steps-to-bring-down-public-debt-sitharaman-11697820374098.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20government%20is%20looking%20at%20ways%20to%20bring%20down%20government%20debt%20and%20is%20monitoring%20the%20debt%20reduction%20measures%20taken%20by%20emerging%20market%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20debt%20stood%20at%20Rs%20155.6%20trillion%2C%20or%2057.1%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20March%202023.%20During%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20debt%20of%20state%20governments%20stood%20at%20about%2028%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20faces%20challenges%20in%20enhancing%20its%20credit%20ratings%20due%20to%20elevated%20debt%20levels%20and%20the%20subst