2_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bank%20%26quot%3Bfroze%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20accounts%26quot%3B%20after%20it%20expanded%20anti-fraud%20controls%20and%20didn't%20provide%20a%20reliable%20and%20quick%20way%20for%20customers%20to%20prove%20their%20identities%20and%20regain%20access%20to%20their%20unemployment%20funds%2C%20the%20CFPB%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20freezes%20U.S.%20Bank%20imposed%20between%20August%20and%20November%202020%2C%20it%20took%20on%20average%20a%20month%20or%20longer%20for%20consumers%20to%20unfreeze%20their%20ReliaCard%20accounts%2C%20the%20regulator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fenforcement%2Factions%2Fus-bank-national-association-prepaid-cards-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20out-of-work%20Americans%20throughout%20the%20country%20had%20little%20choice%20but%20to%20rely%20on%20U.S.%20Bank%20for%20their%20unemployment%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20CFPB%20Director%20Rohit%20Chopra%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BU.S.%20Bank%20blocked%20access%20to%20accounts%20and%20demanded%20burdensome%20paperwork%20in%20order%20for%20consumers%20to%20regain%20access%20to%20their%20frozen%20benefits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20thousands%20of%20other%20customers%20found%20that%20U.S.%20Bank%20failed%20to%20provide%20provisional%20account%20credits%20after%20they%20reported%20unauthorized%20transfers%2C%20the%20CFPB%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBanks%20have%20to%20provide%20provisional%20account%20credits%20if%20their%20investigations%20take%20more%20than%2010%20days%2C%20but%20U.S.%20Bank%20failed%20to%20do%20so%20%26quot%3Bin%20thousands%20of%20cases%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20improperly%20required%20customers%20to%20first%20provide%20additional%20written%20confirmation%20about%20the%20suspected%20unauthorized%20transfers%2C%20the%20CFPB%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Bank%20violated%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Act%20and%20the%20Electronic%20Fund%20Transfer%20Act%2C%20the%20CFPB%20said.%20The%20CFPB%20ordered%20U.S.%20Bank%20to%20pay%20%245.7%20million%20to%20affected%20consumers%20whose%20ReliaCard%20accounts%20were%20frozen%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20%2415%20million%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Office%20of%20the%20Comptroller%20of%20the%20Currency%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.occ.treas.gov%2Fnews-issuances%2Fnews-releases%2F2023%2Fnr-occ-2023-141.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eordered%3C%2Fa%3E%20U.S.%20Bank%20to%20pay%20a%20%2415%20million%20civil%20money%20penalty%2C%20which%20it%20said%20would%20be%20paid%20to%20the%20US%20Treasury%20and%20was%20coordinated%20with%20but%20separate%20from%20the%20CFPB's%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20did%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.consumerfinance.gov%2Ff%2Fdocuments%2Fcfpb_us-bank-stipulation_2023-12.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadmit%20or%20deny%3C%2Fa%3E%20any%20wrongdoing%2C%20the%20CFPB%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20contacted%20U.S.%20Bank%20for%20comment.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20bank%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F12%2F19%2Fus-bank-fined-36-million-for-frozen-unemployment-benefits.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20cardholders%20were%20affected%20due%20to%20extended%20holds%2C%20but%20that%20it%20had%20prevented%20more%20than%20%24375%20million%20of%20fraud%20and%20also%20returned%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20sent%20to%20questionable%20accounts%20to%20the%20states.%20The%20bank%20has%20also%20since%20improved%20its%20ReliaCard%20program%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CFPB%20said%20that%20U.S.%20Bank%2C%20based%20in%20Minneapolis%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20is%20the%20US'%20fifth%20largest%20commercial%20bank.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ba