E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuha%20began%20the%20interview%20with%20a%20very%20interesting%20observation%20that%20underlines%20the%20change%20in%20political%20discourse%20that%20has%20taken%20place%20in%20India%20in%20the%20last%20four%20decades.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20when%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20was%20first%20becoming%20a%20significant%20force%20in%20Indian%20politics%2C%20the%20BJP%20leader%2C%20Lal%20Krishna%20Advani%2C%20said%20he%20stood%20for%20%E2%80%98positive%20secularism%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20forty%20years%20after%20Independence%20secularism%20was%20an%20ideal%20to%20be%20upheld%20and%20cherished%20%E2%80%A6%20now%2C%20however%2C%20no%20major%20politician%20of%20either%20the%20BJP%20or%20the%20Congress%20wishes%20to%20publicly%20avow%20secularism.%20Rather%2C%20they%20want%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20truest%20of%20Hindus.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20a%20change%20of%20acceptable%20discourse%20and%20ideology%20that%20has%20occurred%20since%20the%20late%201980s%20but%20also%2C%20importantly%2C%20a%20very%20sharp%20change%20in%20the%20way%20political%20parties%20present%20themselves.%20%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20BJP%20leaders%20wished%20to%20be%20known%20as%20better%20secularists%20than%20their%20opponents%20in%20the%20Congress.%20Now%2C%20Congress%20leaders%20wish%20to%20be%20known%20as%20more%20devout%20Hindus%20than%20their%20opponents%20in%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%20Guha%20agreed%20that%20whilst%20the%20BJP%20has%20got%20away%20with%20this%20switch%20in%20the%20way%20it%20presents%20itself%2C%20the%20Congress%20seems%20to%20have%20stumbled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20specifically%20about%20the%20Ram%20temple%2C%20which%20is%20due%20to%20be%20inaugurated%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024%2C%20Guha%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20a%20symbol%20of%20religious%20and%20military%20conquest%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20new%20temple%20will%20be%20a%20symbol%20of%20religious%20triumphalism%2C%20a%20sign%20that%20this%20is%20becoming%20ever%20more%20a%20Hindu-first%20country%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20Ram%20temple%20project%20is%20a%20further%20reinforcement%20of%20the%20idea%20that%20India%20is%20above%20all%20a%20Hindu%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuha%20made%20a%20very%20pointed%20comparison%20between%20India%20and%20the%20sort%20of%20country%20India%20is%20becoming%20and%20the%20successful%20countries%20of%20Asia%20such%20as%20Japan%2C%20Singapore%20and%20South%20Korea%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20all%20three%20countries%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20religion%20in%20politics%20and%20public%20life%20is%20extremely%20muted.%E2%80%9D%20In%20India%20it%20is%20increasingly%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20speaking%20about%20himself%2C%20Guha%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20Hindu%20myself%2C%20I%20cannot%20bring%20myself%20to%20celebrate%20this%20new%20temple.%E2%80%9D%20He%20cited%20two%20reasons%20for%20this.%20The%20first%20is%20that%20he%20lived%20in%20North%20India%20during%20those%20bloody%20years%20when%20the%20Babri%20masjid%20was%20destroyed%20and%20thousands%20of%20innocent%20people%2C%20mostly%20Muslims%2C%20lost%20their%20lives%20in%20frenzied%20rioting.%20The%20second%20reason%20he%20does%20not%20celebrate%20the%20temple%20has%20more%20to%20do%20with%20how%20he%20views%20his%20faith.%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20believe%20that%20to%20affirm%20or%20proclaim%20my%20faith%20I%20must%20do%20so%20in%20front%20of%2C%20or%20inside%2C%20a%20colossal%20edifice%20costing%20thousands%20of%20crores%20of%20rupees%20to%20build.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703064948000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20145235%2FKT-20-December.00_43_03_04.Still002.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-ram-temple-india-democracy-pluralism-ram-guha-karan-thapar%22%2