5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20liberty%2C%20a%20non-negotiable%20aspect%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20is%20impeded%20by%20detention%20and%20arbitrary%20arrest.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20sub-human%20and%20morally%20questionable%20treatment%20of%20the%20detainees%20within%20these%20clandestine%20facilities%2C%20strips%20them%20of%20their%20basic%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20team%20conducted%20primary%20field%20interviews%20to%20unpack%20how%20these%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20explores%20how%20these%20detention%20centres%20act%20as%20%E2%80%98sites%20of%20exception%E2%80%99%20and%20push%20individuals%20towards%20rightlessness%2C%20leaving%20those%20labelled%20stateless%20with%20scant%20rights%20to%20shield%20from%20the%20questionable%20treatment.%20The%20name%20of%20the%20interviewee%20has%20been%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaught%20in%20a%20legal%20void%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20her%20own%20experience%20of%20statelessness%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOrigins-Totalitarianism-Hannah-Arendt%2Fdp%2F0156701537%3Fots%3D1%26tag%3Dthneyo0f-20%26linkCode%3Dw50%5C%22%3EHannah%20Arendt%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20that%20the%20requirement%20for%20inclusion%20in%20a%20political%20community%20or%20nation-state%20is%20the%20predicament%20to%20guarantee%20even%20basic%20human%20rights.%20The%20denationalised%2C%20therefore%2C%20experience%20rightlessness%20as%20a%20result%20of%20statelessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20fissures%20of%20globalisation%20resulted%20in%20states%20drawing%20boundaries%2C%20pushing%20huge%20populations%20towards%20the%20periphery%20of%20statelessness%2C%20the%20detention%20centres%20have%20evolved%20as%20spaces%20where%20this%20form%20of%20rightlessness%20is%20worst%20experienced%2C%20with%20no%20guarantee%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20life%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642.png%20760w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642-300x211.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689890%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20classroom%20of%20Forest%20Learning%20Centre%20(FLC)%20at%20Laimuti%20village%2C%20Chirang%20District%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.law.harvard.edu%2Filj%2F2023%2F06%2Ffinding-hope-for-the-hopeless-detention-statelessness-and-international-criminal-law%2F%23_ftnref14%5C%22%3ERefugee%20Convention%20of%201951%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20member%20states%20cannot%20detain%2C%20expel%2C%20or%20return%20immigrants%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20entered%20without%20permission.%20Given%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20member%20state%2C%20it%20is%20not%20bound%20by%20the%20rules%20placed%20by%20the%20Convention%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20it%20has%20been%20seen%20taking%20stringent%20actions%20against%20the%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20through%20detection%2C%20detention%2C%20and%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deplorable%20conditions%20faced%20by%20detainees%20came%20to%20the%20limelight%2C%20particularly%20after%20Harsh%20Mander%2C%20the%20special%20monitor%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%2C%20exposed%20the%20dire%20situation%20within%20the%20camps.%20The%20questionable%20treatment%20inflicted%20upon%20detainees%20is%20perhaps%20best%20exemplified%20by%20the%20case%20of%20Sumi%20Goswami.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumi%20Goswami%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20Matia%20detention%20centre%20on%20account%20of%20a%20technical%20error%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Tribunal.%20Despite%20possessing%20all%20the%20necessary%20documents%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20the%20detention%20camp%20for%20three%20days%2C%20after%20which%20she%20was%20released%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20recounting%20her%20time%20at%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNobody%20would%20understand%20what%20I%20have%20gone%20through.%20Only%20I%20can.%20If%20you%20have%20not%20been%20to%20a%20detention%20camp%2C%20you%20will%20not%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20to%20live%20there.%20Never%20did%20I%20think%20I%20would%20have%20to%20experience%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20living%20conditions%20there%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20about%2014%20to%2015%20people%20within%20one%20cell%2C%20with%20one%20attached%20bathroom.%20The%20first%20day%20I%20went%20there%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20notice%20that%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20bathrooms%20are%20partially%20built%2C%20such%20that%20your%20face%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20outside.%20On%20asking%20an%20official%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20it%20was%20%5Bbuilt%20in%20that%20way%5D%20to%20restrict%20the%20inmates%20from%20committing%20suicides.%20The%20foul%20smell%20from%20the%20bathroom%2C%20because%20of%20the%20partially%20built%20doors%2C%20made%20it%20unbearable%20to%20live%20there%2C%20let%20alone%20eat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoswami%20further%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20could%20not%20sleep%20for%20two%20nights%20straight.%20I%20remained%20seated%20the%20whole%20time.%20Never%20in%20my%20life%20had%20I%20used%20the%20type%20of%20bed%20and%20mattress%20they%20provided%20me%20with.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643.png%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643-300x195.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689891%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22611%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWeavers%20at%20the%20ant%20weaving%20centre%20at%20Rowmari%2C%20Chirang%20District%2C%20Assam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcjp.org.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2FNHRC-Report-Assam-Detention-Centres-26-3-2018-1.pdf%5C%22%3EUNHRC%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20state%20prisons%20should%20not%20be%20used%20for%20detention%2C%20the%20centres%20of%20Assam%20are%20sub-parts%20of%20normal%20jails%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20the%20declared%20%E2%80%9Cforeigners%E2%80%9D%20are%20often%20placed%20within%20the%20same%20cells%20with%20the%20convicted%20prisoners.%20Sumi%20Goswami%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20asked%20one%20of%20the%20inmates%20what%20she%20was%20doing%20there%20and%20she%20said%20she%20murdered%20her%20brother%20for%20land.%20I%20asked%20another%20woman%20the%20same%20question%20and%20she%20said%20she%20was%20arrested%20for%20smuggling%20drugs.%20How%20can%20you%20sleep%20peacefully%20in%20a%20room%20with%20criminals%20around%20you%3F%20Someone%20might%20come%20and%20kill%20you%2C%20you%20never%20know.%20Why%20are%20the%20D-voters%20kept%20with%20these%20criminals%3F%20What%20crime%20did%20they%20commit%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumi%20sighed%20as%20she%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20one%20of%20the%20inmates%20told%20me%20that%20she%20was%20living%20there%20for%20ten%20years%2C%20I%20was%20shocked.%20I%20would%20not%20be%20alive%20if%20I%20had%20to%20live%20there%20forever.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20all%20detainees%20are%20compelled%20to%20live%20in%20substandard%20conditions%2C%20women%20experience%20even%20worse%20conditions%2C%20including%20complaints%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20and%20forced%20abortions%2C%20among%20other%20forms%20of%20violence.%20The%20differential%20experiences%20of%20women%20in%20detention%20will%20be%20dealt%20with%20in%20the%20next%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20comprehensive%20legal%20framework%20must%20be%20established%2C%20ensuring%20the%20fair%20and%20humane%20treatment%20of%20detainees%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20immigration%20status.%20Resolving%20legal%20ambiguities%2C%20providing%20an%20adequate%20legal%20defence%2C%20and%20addressing%20the%20specific%20vulnerabilities%20of%20detainees%20are%20essential%20steps%20to%20bring%20detention%20practices%20in%20Assam%20in%20line%20with%20international%20human%20rights%20standards.%20The%20urgency%20of%20this%20task%20is%20underscored%20by%20the%20profound%20impact%20on%20the%20lives%20and%20well-being%20of%20those%20affected%20by%20the%20current%20state%20of%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20photographs%20have%20been%20taken%20by%20CNES%20researchers%20during%20field%20work%20in%20Assam.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Samragnee%20Chakraborty%20and%20Hima%20Trisha%20M.%20are%20Senior%20Research%20Analysts%20(CNES).%20Yashovardhan%20Chaturvedi%2C%20Nitya%20Arora%2C%20Rieshav%20Chakraborty%20and%20Aman%20Chain%20are%20Research%20Assistants%20with%20CNES.%20The%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Salah%20Punathil%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%20for%20his%20guidance%20and%20support.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20by%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20explores%20the%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20as%20spaces%20violating%20human%20rights%20and%20disproportionately%20affecting%20migrants.%20These%20are%20penned%20down%20from%20the%20documented%20findings%20of%20a%20recent%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20edition.%20Click%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazaadawaazcnes.wordpress.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20access%20the%20work%20of%20Azaad%20Awaaz%2C%20an%20initiative%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20working%20on%20issues%20of%20social%20exclusion%2C%20marginalization%2C%20and%20discrimination%20experienced%20by%20vulnerable%2C%20precarious%20communities%20across%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703062822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20131757%2Fimage-1646.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sumi%20Goswami%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20Matia%20detention%20centre%20on%20account%20of%20a%20technical%20error%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Tribunal.%20Her%20three-day%20experience%20at%20the%20centre%20exposes%20the%20inhumane%20treatment%20of%20detainees%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20immigration%20status.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sensex%20crashes%20over%201%2C000%20pts%3A%20Why%20stock%20mkt%20is%20down%20today%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703062462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt